Problem Statement

Create a Java application using hierarchical inheritance. Create a base class named Person and derive two classes namely Student and Faculty. 
Display the details of both the student and the faculty.

class Person {

    String college = "KSR College";

}

class Student extends Person {

    String name = "Raghul";
    int regNo = 59;
    String department = "ECE";

    void studentDetails() {
        System.out.println("Student Details");
        System.out.println("----------------------");
        System.out.println("Name       : " + name);
        System.out.println("Register No: " + regNo);
        System.out.println("Department : " + department);
        System.out.println("College    : " + college);
    }
}

class Faculty extends Person {

    String facultyName = "Arun Kumar";
    String subject = "Java Programming";

    void facultyDetails() {
        System.out.println();
        System.out.println("Faculty Details");
        System.out.println("----------------------");
        System.out.println("Faculty Name : " + facultyName);
        System.out.println("Subject      : " + subject);
        System.out.println("College      : " + college);
    }
}

public class CollegeManagement {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Student s = new Student();
        Faculty f = new Faculty();

        s.studentDetails();
        f.facultyDetails();

    }
}

